"point nodal. Le point nodal doit être capable de formuler une stratégie "
"générale et des *programmes de travail* en conformité avec les priorités du "
"Participant. Ces programmes devraient définir les attentes concernant les "
"résultats générés par le point nodal dans une durée donnée, et aideront à "
"évaluer les performances du point nodal."

#. type: Title =====
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Engagement Capacity"
msgstr "Capacité d’engagement"

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:27
msgid "The ability to initiate and sustain partnerships and networks."
msgstr "Aptitude à initier et à maintenir des partenariats et des réseaux."

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:30
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "A collaborative framework to form a biodiversity information facility, defined and agreed to by the relevant stakeholders and partners within the Participant’s domain. This framework should ensure that the node has a well-defined role within the landscape of biodiversity-related institutions, based on strong partnerships and complementary services (see section 6.1). It should include relevant formal agreements around data publishing and data access. It should also ensure that the node recognizes and values its constituent organizations and individuals that contribute to and use its services, in order to build good relationships with them."
msgid "**A collaborative framework** to form a biodiversity information facility, defined and agreed to by the relevant stakeholders and partners within the Participant’s domain. This framework should ensure that the node has a well-defined role within the landscape of biodiversity-related institutions, based on strong partnerships and complementary services \\(see section 6.1\\). It should include community norms and relevant formal agreements around data publishing and data access. It should also ensure that the node recognizes and values its constituent organizations and individuals that contribute to and use its services, in order to build good relationships with them.  \n"
msgstr "Un *cadre collaboratif* permettant de mettre en place un système d’information sur la biodiversité, défini et préétabli par les parties prenantes et les partenaires concernés au sein du domaine d’activité du Participant. Ce cadre devrait garantir que le point nodal possède un rôle bien défini au sein de l’ensemble des institutions sur la biodiversité, s’appuyant sur des partenariats solides et des services complémentaires (cf. _Section 6.1_). Il doit inclure des accords formels pertinents sur la publication et l’accès aux données. Il doit également s’assurer que le point nodal reconnaît et valorise les organisations et les individus qui en sont membres, qui y contribuent et utilisent ses services afin de consolider ses relations avec eux."

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:31
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Communications and outreach plans, tools and materials to support collaborative work between the members of the node’s network and to encourage the ongoing addition of new members. Materials can include a website, newsletters, brochures, mailing lists and use of social media platforms. The https://www.gbif.org/document/80926[GBIF communications strategy] can help identify key messages for relevant audiences, and Participants can coordinate with the Secretariat on communication activities within the wider GBIF network."
msgid "**Communications and outreach plans, tools and materials** to support collaborative work between the members of the node’s network and to encourage the ongoing addition of new members. Materials can include a website, newsletters, brochures, mailing lists and use of social media platforms. The [GBIF communications strategy](https://www.gbif.org/document/80926) can help identify key messages for relevant audiences, and Participants can coordinate with the Secretariat on communication activities within the wider GBIF network.\n"
msgstr "Des *plans, outils et matériaux de communication et de sensibilisation* pour contribuer au travail collaboratif entre les membres du réseau du point nodal et pour encourager l’adhésion continuelle de nouveaux membres. Les matériaux peuvent comprendre un site Internet, des bulletins d’information, des brochures, des listes de diffusion et l’utilisation de plateformes de médias sociaux. La https://www.gbif.org/document/80926[stratégie de communication du GBIF] (_en anglais_) peut aider à identifier les messages principaux devant être transmis aux publics concernés, et les participants peuvent coordonner avec le Secrétariat des activités de communication dans l’ensemble du réseau GBIF."

#. type: Title =====
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Implementation and Evaluation Capacity"
msgstr "Capacité de mise en oeuvre et d’évaluation"

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:36
msgid ""
"The ability to manage, fund, budget, implement and evaluate projects and "
"programmes."
msgstr ""
"Aptitude à gérer, financer, budgéter, mettre en oeuvre et évaluer des "
"projets et des programmes."

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:39
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Dedicated staff members to implement the node’s mandate and work plans (see section 6.2). The node team will require a broad range of skills, ranging from biodiversity informatics to network coordination and supported by appropriate training."
msgid "**Dedicated staff members** to implement the node’s mandate and work plans (see section 6.2). The node team will require a broad range of skills, ranging from biodiversity informatics to network coordination and supported by appropriate training.  \n"
msgstr "Des *membres du personnel dédiés* pour mettre en oeuvre le mandat et les programmes de travail du point nodal (cf. _Section 6.2_). L’équipe du point nodal aura besoin d’un large éventail de compétences allant de l’informatique appliquée à la biodiversité à la coordination de réseau, soutenues par une formation appropriée."

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:40
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Institutional and financial support, in line with services the node is expected to provide and to support the delivery of the node’s work plans. Institutional support can include administrative assistance, hosting facilities, and political endorsement necessary to engage key partners, raise interest and visibility, and mobilize funds."
msgid "**Institutional and financial support**, in line with services the node is expected to provide and to support the delivery of the node’s work plans. Institutional support can include administrative assistance, hosting facilities, and political endorsement necessary to engage key partners, raise interest and visibility, and mobilize funds. \n"
msgstr "Une *aide institutionnelle et financière* en conformité avec les services devant être fournis par le point nodal pour que le point nodal puisse réaliser ses programmes de travail. L’aide institutionnelle peut comprendre une assistance administrative, des installations hôtes et le soutien politique nécessaire pour permettre l’implication de partenaires clés, susciter l’intérêt, accroître la visibilité et mobiliser des fonds."

#. type: Title ====
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "Technical capacities"
msgstr "Capacités techniques"

#. type: Title =====
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Biodiversity data mobilization"
msgstr "Mobilisation des données sur la biodiversité"

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:48
msgid "The ability to collect, digitize and publish biodiversity data."
msgstr ""
"Aptitude à collecter, numériser et publier les données sur la biodiversité."

#. type: Plain text
#: 5.-what-do-participant-nodes-need-to-be-effective/5.1-basic-requirements.en.adoc:51
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "An informatics infrastructure to support the mobilization of biodiversity "
#| "data. Existing tools, such as the https://www.gbif.org/ipt[Integrated "
